<h2 id="tricky-adjectives">Tricky Adjectives That Fool Learners</h2>

<div style="background:#fef3c7; border:1px solid #fde68a; border-radius:12px; padding:1.5rem; margin:1.5rem 0;">
  <p style="font-weight:700; margin-bottom:0.75rem;">na-Adjectives That Look Like i-Adjectives</p>
  <ul style="margin:0; padding-left:1.25rem;">
    <li><strong>きれい</strong> (kirei) — beautiful → きれい<strong>な</strong>花 (NOT きれい花)</li>
    <li><strong>嫌い</strong> (kirai) — disliked → 嫌い<strong>な</strong>食べ物</li>
    <li><strong>有名</strong> (yuumei) — famous → 有名<strong>な</strong>人</li>
    <li><strong>幸い</strong> (saiwai) — fortunate → na-adjective</li>
  </ul>
  <p style="margin:0.75rem 0 0; font-size:0.9rem; color:#92400e;">Rule of thumb: If the い is part of a kanji reading (not a standalone い ending), it's likely a na-adjective.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="sentence-patterns">Adjective Sentence Patterns</h2>

<div style="background:#f8fafc; border:1px solid #e2e8f0; border-radius:12px; padding:1.5rem; margin:1.5rem 0;">
  <p style="font-weight:700; margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Pattern 1: [Noun] は [Adjective] です</p>
  <p style="margin:0.25rem 0;">この本は面白いです。<span style="color:#64748b;"> — This book is interesting.</span></p>
  <p style="margin:0.25rem 0;">日本語は難しいです。<span style="color:#64748b;"> — Japanese is difficult.</span></p>

  <p style="font-weight:700; margin:1rem 0 0.75rem;">Pattern 2: [Adjective] + [Noun] (modifying nouns)</p>
  <p style="margin:0.25rem 0;">高いレストラン <span style="color:#64748b;"> — expensive restaurant</span></p>
  <p style="margin:0.25rem 0;">静かな場所 <span style="color:#64748b;"> — quiet place</span></p>

  <p style="font-weight:700; margin:1rem 0 0.75rem;">Pattern 3: Connecting adjectives (te-form)</p>
  <p style="margin:0.25rem 0;">安くて美味しい。<span style="color:#64748b;"> — Cheap and delicious.</span></p>
  <p style="margin:0.25rem 0;">静かできれいな部屋。<span style="color:#64748b;"> — A quiet and beautiful room.</span></p>

  <p style="font-weight:700; margin:1rem 0 0.75rem;">Pattern 4: Comparison with より</p>
  <p style="margin:0.25rem 0;">東京は大阪より大きいです。<span style="color:#64748b;"> — Tokyo is bigger than Osaka.</span></p>
  <p style="margin:0;">日本語は英語より難しいです。<span style="color:#64748b;"> — Japanese is harder than English.</span></p>
</div>

<p>Adjectives are building blocks for expressing opinions, descriptions, and comparisons. Practice them with our <a href="/japanese/tools/jlpt-vocabulary/">JLPT Vocabulary Browser</a> and use the <a href="/japanese/tools/particle-guide/">Particle Guide</a> to understand how adjectives interact with particles. For more grammar fundamentals, check our <a href="/japanese/blog/japanese-particles-explained/">particles guide</a> and <a href="/japanese/blog/japanese-verb-conjugation/">verb conjugation guide</a>.</p>

